The malicious flash file 8hthrx.swf (MD5 faa74be286c58be616470558d78a137f) checks the user's operating system (OS) and browser version. If the OS is Windows XP, it targets either Firefox or Internet Explorer; otherwise it only targets Internet Explorer.
The file (MD5 faa74be286c58be616470558d78a137f) was LZMA compressed and the payload was obfuscated using a one byte XOR key. Underlying the XOR is an embedded executable and the following callback URLs.
http://iad12s04-in-f22.1h100.net http://iad12s04-in-f22.1h100.net/pv.png http://iad12s04-in-f22.1h100.net/cmd_postback.php http://iad12s04-in-f22.1h100.net/init_postback.php http://iad12s04-in-f99.1h100.net/pv.png
